              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Structure",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The function returns a string representation of the input number, padded with leading zeros to ensure the total length is three characters. For example, an input of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "5",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
